  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 18 June 1925
---
For me, politics bereft of religion is absolute dirt ever to be
shunned. Politics concern nations and that which concerns the welfare of
nations must be one of the concerns of a man who is religiously inclined,
in other words a seeker after God and Truth.
